'''Maureen Ann Collins''' (born July 7, 1965)<ref>{{IMDb name|0172558|Mo Collins}}</ref> is an [[United States|American]] [[actress]] and [[comedian]], known professionally as Mo Collins. She is perhaps best known for being a member of the ensemble on [[Fox Broadcasting Company|FOX's]] [[sketch comedy]] series ''[[Mad TV]]''. Collins became well known for several characters during her tenure on the show.
She was a cast member from the 4th season (1998) through the 9th season (2004); she only appeared in fourteen episodes during season 9 due to contractual reasons. She returned to ''Mad TV'' in the 10th season for one episode, and again when she made an appearance on the 300th episode doing her popular character Lorraine Swanson. Her best known role following her departure from ''Mad TV'' was as morning talk show host [[List of Parks and Recreation characters#Joan Callamezzo|Joan Callamezzo]] on the sitcom ''[[Parks and Recreation]]''.
==Career==
===''Mad TV''=== Collins joined the cast of ''[[Mad TV]]'' at the beginning of season 4 (Fall 1998) and stayed until the end of season 9 (Spring 2004), despite appearing in only 14 episodes during the ninth season. Her popular stint on the show led her to come back to guest star in 2005 during Season 10, in 2007 during the 300th episode on season 13, final episode of season 14 in 2009 and the 20th anniversary reunion special in 2016. She was also known for trying to stifle laughter during some of her skits much like [[Harvey Korman]] on ''[[The Carol Burnett Show]]''. {{citation needed|date=October 2014}}
Her most featured and arguably most popular characters were Doreen, the screechy-voiced mother of overgrown toddler Stuart (when Mo Collins left the show, Doreen was written off as being asleep after her latest alcoholic bender or never mentioned); the odd, annoying, confused middle-aged woman Lorraine, and the perpetually unlucky Trina.
Collins also did a multitude of celebrity impressions, including [[Pamela Anderson]], [[Barbara Bush]], [[Cher]], [[Hillary Clinton]], [[Courteney Cox]], [[Judy Garland]] (as [[Dorothy Gale]] from ''[[The Wizard of Oz (1939 film)|The Wizard of Oz]]''), [[Jenilee Harrison]], [[Mary Hart]], [[Teri Hatcher]], [[Ann Heche]], [[Catherine Hicks]], [[Angelina Jolie]], [[Jenny Jones (presenter)|Jenny Jones]], [[Jane Kaczmarek]] (as Lois on a ''[[Malcolm in the Middle]]'' parody called ''[[Malcolm X]] in the Middle''), [[Dina Lohan]], [[Andie MacDowell]], [[Madonna (entertainer)|Madonna]], [[Penny Marshall]] (as herself and as Laverne DeFazio from ''[[Laverne & Shirley]]''), [[Audrey Meadows]], [[Mary Tyler Moore]] (in several "modern day spin" parodies of ''[[The Mary Tyler Moore Show]]''), [[Alanis Morissette]], [[Pink (singer)|Pink]], [[Diane Sawyer]], [[Shakira]], [[Martha Stewart]], [[Shania Twain]], and [[Catherine Zeta-Jones]].
===Other credits=== * She plays Starla, a business model-turned-secretary, on Season 2 of ''[[Arrested Development (TV series)|Arrested Development]]''. * She plays a nurse with a big vagina in ''[[Curb Your Enthusiasm]]'' ("The Ski Lift", season 5, episode 8). * She plays a speed dater named Gina {{IPAc-en|ˈ|dʒ|aɪ|n|ə}}, in a small role in the [[Judd Apatow]] film ''[[The 40-Year-Old Virgin]]''. * She plays a doctor in a small role in the [[Judd Apatow]] film ''[[Knocked Up]]''. *She has performed a NITY-woman show, ''Mo vs. Mo'', in various cities, including [[Los Angeles]] and [[Chicago]].{{cn|date=October 2016}} * She played iTeacher (a teacher who gives her lessons via a live [[podcast]] because of her fear of being in front of students) on the [[Nickelodeon]] [[sitcom]] ''[[Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide]]''. *Collins voiced the character "Robo-Mom" and Zita on the Nickelodeon cartoon, ''[[Invader Zim]]''. The celebrity she impersonated was the singer [[Faith Hill]]. * Collins plays on the [[World Poker Tour]] in the Hollywood Home games for the We Spark charity.{{cn|date=October 2016}}
*She performed with Streetmosphere at the (formerly named) [[Disney-MGM Studios]] in the Hollywood Public Works.{{cn|date=October 2016}} * She voices Jan Ors in the ''Star Wars: Dark Forces: The Collector's Trilogy'' audio drama.{{cn|date=October 2016}} * She reprised her [[Mary Tyler Moore]] impression on an episode of former MADtv castmate [[Frank Caliendo]]'s ''[[Frank TV]]''. * She played the role of Emily on the ABC sitcom ''[[According to Jim]]''. * She had a semi-recurring role on NBC's sitcom ''[[Parks and Recreation]]'' as Joan Callamezzo, the host of the local [[talk show]] ''Pawnee Today''. * She provides the voices of Ella, Abigail, and Frida on Disney Junior's cartoon ''[[Sheriff Callie's Wild West]]''. * She voices Dispatch in ''[[Batman Unlimited: Animal Instincts]]''. * She provides multiple voices on the [[Netflix]] animated comedy ''[[F is for Family]]''. * She portrays recurring character Susan on the Netflix comedy ''[[Lady Dynamite (TV series)|Lady Dynamite]]''. * She voiced Strider the Sheepdog from [[Puppy Dog Pals]], in the episodes, Counting Sheep and Rhapsody in Pug. Not only she voiced Strider, but Harriet the Elephant from Puzzling Pugs, and Newf the Lake Dog from Hystery Mistory. * She played Tanya, mother of main character of Chelsea Snap, in season 3 of the [[TV Land]] sitcom ''[[Teachers (2016 TV series)|Teachers]]''. * She has been cast as Sarah in [[Fear_the_Walking_Dead_(season_4)|Season 4]] of ''[[Fear The Walking Dead]]''.
==Personal life== Collins is in remission from a rare form of cancer known as [[gastrointestinal stromal tumor]] (GIST). <!-- 5 years in remission needed to be cured -->She was diagnosed in spring 2011 when she noticed an odd lump in her abdomen. Said Collins: "I would have done nothing about it. I was 44, feeling healthy, everything was going great for me, but my fiancé, Alex said, ‘You need to get it checked out’". She learned she had a primary tumor in her [[duodenum]] and was able to find a doctor who knew enough to know that she needed to see a specialist.<ref>{{cite web| url= http://liferaftgroup.org/2013/04/mo-collins-battle-with-gist |title= Who’s laughing now? Actress Mo Collins uses humor in her battle with GIST| first= Erin |last= Kristoff | website= liferaftgroup.org| date= April 1, 2013| accessdate= October 26, 2014}}</ref>
Collins has been married to actor [[Alex Skuby]] since June 2013.<ref>{{cite web| url= https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0804923/bio | website= IMDb.com| publisher= Internet Movie Database| title= Mo Collins Biography page}}</ref>They have no children.
